  <!-- ================== STEPPER DRIVE ================== -->
  <div class="schematic-section">
    <h2>3. STEPPER MOTOR DRIVE CIRCUIT</h2>
    <div class="component-diagram">
SPECIFICATIONS:
- Stepper: NEMA 17 (200 steps/rev)
- Driver: A4988 or DRV8825
- Microstepping: Full step (MS1=MS2=MS3=GND)
- Firmware step rate: 0.2 steps/s
- Rotation period: 1000 s per revolution
- Spin frequency: f_spin = 0.001 Hz
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ================== OPTICAL LEVER ================== -->
  <div class="schematic-section">
    <h2>4. OPTICAL LEVER READOUT</h2>
    <div class="component-diagram">
R1 = 330Ω (ONLY if laser module lacks internal current limiting)
Photodiode: BPW34
ADC: Arduino A0
    </div>

    <div class="notes">
      <strong>NOTE:</strong> Most 5 V laser modules include internal current limiting.
      If so, omit R1 and connect directly to Arduino 5 V and GND.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ================== CALIBRATION COIL ================== -->
  <div class="schematic-section">
    <h2>5. MAGNETIC CALIBRATION COIL</h2>
    <div class="component-diagram">
MOSFET: IRLZ44N (logic-level)
Pulse: ~100 ms (firmware-defined)

TORQUE ESTIMATION
(NON-CALIBRATED, ORDER-OF-MAGNITUDE ONLY):
- Estimated τ ≈ 10⁻⁶ N·m
- Geometry-dependent
- Must be calibrated experimentally
    </div>
